// invalid for parser: a struct field with an initializer (struct fields are
// declared, not initialized). The recovery must report the bad field and
// still close the struct, so the rest of the file parses. Two errors expected:
// the bad field's '=', and the sync's "expected fn/struct/global" if recovery
// overshoots - the point of this test is that the struct DOES error (a
// regression where struct-field init silently parsed as a valid field would
// let this pass, which is wrong).
struct Bad { x: i64 = 5; }
fn main() -> i64 { return 0; }
